			<p class="comment-author">
				<span class="comment-author-name">Jeanne P Benedict</span> <span class="says">says</span>			</p>

			<p class="comment-meta"><time class="comment-time">April 02, 2023 at 6:57 pm</time></p>		</header>

		<div class="comment-content">
			
			<p>Awesome meal that I will make again! Dinner party worthy! I almost got tripped up by "add the cloves" thinking cloves was an ingredient but then I realized it was garlic cloves!</p>
		</div>

		<div class="comment-reply"><a rel="nofollow" class="comment-reply-link" href="#comment-8859" data-commentid="8859" data-postid="16517" data-belowelement="article-comment-8859" data-respondelement="respond" data-replyto="Reply to Jeanne P Benedict" aria-label="Reply to Jeanne P Benedict">Reply</a></div>
		
	</article>
	<ul class="children">

	<li class="comment byuser comment-author-bdebolt bypostauthor even depth-2" id="comment-8868">
	<article id="article-comment-8868">

		
		<header class="comment-header">
			<p class="comment-author">
				<span class="comment-author-name">Briana</span> <span class="says">says</span>			</p>

			<p class="comment-meta"><time class="comment-time">April 03, 2023 at 11:42 am</time></p>		</header>

		<div class="comment-content">
			
			<p>This is so awesome to hear, Jeanne! Good catch - I've updated the recipe card to state "garlic cloves". Sometimes I just start typing a little too fast. 😉 So glad you enjoyed!</p>
		</div>

		<div class="comment-reply"><a rel="nofollow" class="comment-reply-link" href="#comment-8868" data-commentid="8868" data-postid="16517" data-belowelement="article-comment-8868" data-respondelement="respond" data-replyto="Reply to Briana" aria-label="Reply to Briana">Reply</a></div>
		
	</article>
	</li><!-- #comment-## -->
</ul><!-- .children -->
</li><!-- #comment-## -->

	<li class="comment odd alt thread-odd thread-alt depth-1" id="comment-8028">
	<article id="article-comment-8028">

		
		<header class="comment-header">
			<p class="comment-author">
				<span class="comment-author-name">Kristin</span> <span class="says">says</span>			</p>

			<p class="comment-meta"><time class="comment-time">January 25, 2023 at 8:08 am</time></p>		</header>

		<div class="comment-content">
			
			<p><img class="wprm-comment-rating" src="data:image/gif;base64,R0lGODdhAQABAPAAAP///wAAACwAAAAAAQABAEACAkQBADs=" data-lazy-src="https://afullliving.com/wp-content/plugins/wp-recipe-maker/assets/icons/rating/stars-alt-5.svg" alt="5 stars" width="80" height="16" /><br />
Admittedly, I used this as a base recipe to use up some things I had in the fridge.  Thus, I swapped out ricotta for the heavy cream, through in some homemade pesto (which had been frozen for a few years) and used about 1/2 cup vermouth with 1/2 cup chicken stock.  I also deboned and skinned the thighs and adjusted times accordingly.   Final result was great over egg noodles.  I hope to make this again (as written) because even with my randomish changes, it was delicious.</p>
		</div>

		<div class="comment-reply"><a rel="nofollow" class="comment-reply-link" href="#comment-8028" data-commentid="8028" data-postid="16517" data-belowelement="article-comment-8028" data-respondelement="respond" data-replyto="Reply to Kristin" aria-label="Reply to Kristin">Reply</a></div>
		
	</article>
	<ul class="children">

	<li class="comment byuser comment-author-bdebolt bypostauthor even depth-2" id="comment-8030">
	<article id="article-comment-8030">

		
		<header class="comment-header">
			<p class="comment-author">
				<span class="comment-author-name">Briana</span> <span class="says">says</span>			</p>

			<p class="comment-meta"><time class="comment-time">January 25, 2023 at 12:30 pm</time></p>		</header>

		<div class="comment-content">
			
			<p>Love how creative you got with what you hand on hand, that sounds fabulous! Thanks for the awesome comment, Kristin! 🙂</p>
		</div>

		<div class="comment-reply"><a rel="nofollow" class="comment-reply-link" href="#comment-8030" data-commentid="8030" data-postid="16517" data-belowelement="article-comment-8030" data-respondelement="respond" data-replyto="Reply to Briana" aria-label="Reply to Briana">Reply</a></div>
		
